               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1372" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1372" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1372" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1372" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD SMITH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a warehouseman in Grocers'-hall-court, Poultry. John Eiger, jun, was in my employ—I had seen his father at my place twice—I had about one hundred carpet bags—on the 3rd of Oct. I missed some—I spoke to John Elger, jun., about them—he denied all knowledge of them—I went to his father's house on the 4th of Oct., and said to him, "This is a</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184310230187"></xptr>
               <p>pretty mess John has got into about the carpet bags"—he came down and asked his son if he knew anything about them—he said he did sot—Elger, the father, said that he could lay down his life and his existence that his son was innocent—I have found forty-seven of them—these four are mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1373" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1373" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1373" type="surname" value="WHITTAKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1373" type="given" value="STEPHEN"></interp>STEPHEN WHITTAKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker. These four carpet bags were pawned on the 23rd Sept., by John Elger, sen.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1374" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1374" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1374" type="surname" value="MORRELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1374" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MORRELL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constabe G</hi> 60.) I went to the house—both the prisoners were there—I took them to the station, and charged them with the felony—on the way back to the house, the father said, "It is very hard to accuse an innocent man, I have never seen them"—I was looking about for the duplicates, and the son said, "You need not look, you will find no tioket of the bags, I can tell you"—I did not find any.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">John Elger, sen.</hi> I have a wife and nine children—I have been for the last eighteen months in utter distress.</p>
